The geniuses at Facebook (Our favorite Possibly Not Completely Evilâ¢ company) have created a library called React, which makes the process of building web user interfaces totally more awesomer! You can get started with this right away, here's all you need to do (gotta pee? Don't worry, I promise this will be quick):

1. Install Node and NPM

2. Create a project directory and type npm init into your terminal to create a package.json file

3. Use npm to install the React and ReactDOM modules

4. Install babel-core, babel-loader and babel-preset-react to compile JSX into JavaScript

5. Create a babel configuration file named .babelrc containing the following code:

{ presets: ['react'] }

6. Install webpack, webpack-dev-server and html-webpack-plugin

7. Create a webpack configuration file named webpack.config.js with the following code:

module.exports = {
  entry: __dirname + '/app/index.js',
  module: {
    loaders: [
      {
        test: /\.js$/,
        exclude: /node_modules/,
        loader: 'babel-loader'
      }
    ]
  },
  output: {
    filename: 'transformed.js',
    path: __dirname + '/build'
  }
};

8. Configure HTMLWebpackPlugIn by adding the following to the top of webpack.config.js:

var HTMLWebpackPlugIn = require('html-webpack-plugin');
var HTMLWebpackPlugInConfig = new HTMLWebpackPlugIn({
  template: __dirname + '/app/index.html',
  filename: 'index.html',
  inject: 'body'
});

9. Add the HTMLWebpackPlugin instance to module.exports as the following property:

plugins: [HTMLWebpackPluginConfig]
};

10. Add the following npm script to package.json:

scripts: {
  build: "webpack",
  start: "webpack-dev-server"
}

11. Perform webpack transformations by typing:

npm run build

12. Start a local server with the command:

npm run start

13. Create a new directory named app inside your root directory containing a file named
index.html with the following code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title Local React App</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="app"></div>
</body>
</html>

14. Create index.js with:

var React = require('react');
var ReactDOM = require('react-dom');
var App =
require('./components/App');

ReactDOM.render(
    <App />,
     document.getElementById('app')
 );

15. Create a folder named components inside your app folder. In app/components/App.js, write a component class. This component class can render whatever you want. Don't forget to require React at the top of the file, and to set module.exports equal to your component class at the bottom of the file.

16. In the terminal, type:

npm run build

This will create your new html and js files.

17. Type:

npm run start

18. Navigate to http://localhost:8080 in your browser.

Congratulations! Now you can start your project!
